{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/layouts"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Some components can be used for ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"layouts"}]},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"title":"Layouts","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}],"role":"article"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"anchor":"Colored-Surface","level":3,"text":"Colored Surface","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Colored backgrounds use surface colors to maximize the contrast with content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The colors of several OUDS components (for instance ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true},{"text":") are automatically adjusted if they are placed on ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To do so, some tokens associated with these specific colors can be customized and are identified with the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" suffix (for instance ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"buttonColorBgDefaultEnabledMono"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" of ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OrangeThemeButtonComponentTokensProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-it-works","level":4,"text":"How it works","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"According to the color, the "},{"code":"OUDSColoredSurface","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component adds in SwiftUI environment two flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"oudsUseMonochrome","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": to inform a component that needs to use mono version of tokens","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsOnColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":": to inform a component it is placed on colored surface even if the mono is off"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-to-use","level":4,"text":"How to use","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The folowing view has a colored background \"modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized\" with","    \/\/ - a text with the color adapted according to the adjusted colorScheme      ","    \/\/ - a button that uses the mono version of tokens","","    \/\/ As view","    OUDSColoredSurface(color: theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized) {","        VStack {","            Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","            .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","            OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","        }","    }","","    \/\/ As view modifier","","    VStack {","        Text(\"Status Positive Emphasized\")","        .oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorContentDefault)","","        OUDSButton(text: \"Button\") {}","    }","    .oudsColoredSurface(theme.colorModes.modeOnStatusPositiveEmphasized)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Debuging-contrast-ratios","level":5,"text":"Debuging contrast ratios","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", also named “RGAA”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is highly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for texts and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some components like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":" ; thus in that case we can know the surface color for a given component on it, and compute the contrast ratio, and in the end display or not warnings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To do that, some steps must be followed in your component implementation:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rise the flag to allow debugging (e.g. i #DEBUG mode)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the environement variable defined by the colored surface containing the applied color"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the component implementation, add a line of code comparing the color to test and that surface"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then keep an eye on your logs ; warnings will be added there if WCAG 2.1 3:1, 4.5:1 or 7:1 ratios are not reached, depending to the methods you call"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Rise the flag","#if DEBUG","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.oudsDebugWCAG21Colors = true","#endif","","\/\/ Supposing we are in your component View \/ ViewModifer struct","","\/\/ Get the applied surface color","@Environment(\\.oudsSurfaceColor) var surfaceColor","","\/\/ In the function defining the color to apply, add the line below","\/\/ where colorTokenToApply is the color to apply from a theme:","","\/\/ Non-textual components, in AA","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .nonTextual)","","\/\/ Textual components and AAA to check","OUDSWCAG21Ratios.debugContrastRatio(colorToApply, surfaceColor, .AAA)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Divider","anchor":"Divider"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How it works","anchor":"How-it-works"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider is used to separate content elements in a view. Two kinds of divider are proposed:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked vertivally (VStask).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"OUDSVerticalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" To separate elements stacked Horizontally (HStask).","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A divider can be colored using color enumerated in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSDividerColor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"type":"heading","text":"How to use","anchor":"How-to-use"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Add a vertical divider between items","HStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSVerticalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}","","\/\/ Add an horizontal divider between items","VStack {","    Text(\"Hello wolrd!\")","    OUDSHorizontalDivider(color: .brandPrimary)","    Text(\"Happy to see you\")","}"],"syntax":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The catalog of all components provided by OUDS. It contains also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewModifiers"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply tokens and styles on components and higher-level views."}],"kind":"symbol","title":"OUDSComponents","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSColoredSurface":{"type":"topic","title":"OUDSColoredSurface","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSColoredSurface"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSColoredSurface"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSColoredSurface","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscoloredsurface","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Used to define if a content is used on a colored surface."}]},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSButton":{"title":"OUDSButton","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbutton","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSButton","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" proposes layout with text only, icon only or text with icon."}]},"https://accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr/":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Référentiel Général d’Amélioration de l’Accessibilité"}],"url":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","title":"Référentiel Général d’Amélioration de l’Accessibilité","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr\/","type":"link"},"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSLink":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudslink","type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"OUDSLink","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSLink","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSLink","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" proposes layout with text only or text with icon.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It also proposes layout to navigate forward or backward. The link can be displayed in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"small"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"default"},{"type":"text","text":" size."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSLink","kind":"identifier"}]}}}